tweet: A nuclear bomb is a combination of a hurricane, firestorm, earthquake, and a nuclear meltdown, all conveniently wrapped up as a ICBM.  No help is coming for anyone left in the city.  Hospitals would have been leveled, along with any doctors or medical staff in them.  20/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: Over the next few hours to days, many thousands more will die from acute radiation sickness.  Characterized by a slow loss of function, with internal organs liquefying, many will die in slow agony with no help coming.  19/🧵

tweet: As the mushroom cloud reaches it's maximum height, and depending on weather condition, a rain starts to fall, carrying down radioactive particles and ash.  This black rain coats everything, and gets inside the lungs of people, dosing them with lethal radiation.  18/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: Even if one was able to shelter in subway stations or tunnels, there's nothing that's friendly to them above.  With the risk of flooding, these people will eventually make it top side to an apocalyptic scene of carnage.  17/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: Hundreds of thousands, maybe even millions, will have broken bones, concussions, third-degree burns, be crushed, lacerated, and be discombobulated.  That's the lie. Emergency response is dependent on existing infrastructure.  16/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: The breakdown of infrastructure. Take any natural disaster in the past — hurricanes, wildfires, earthquakes. There's always an immediate response; search and rescue, and people flocking to help.  Not this time.  15/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: Unfortunately, they're unaware that the shockwave is still travelling at them, ready to shred them in a blizzard of shattered glass.  The third and most horrifying of phases takes its sweet time.  14/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: Depending on the city, the plethora of oxygen can spark an inferno that burns the rubble, and by extension, everyone trapped in it or trying to get away from it.  As far as 22 km's away, ordinary people rush to capture footage of the blast and the mushroom cloud.  13/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: The famous mushroom cloud forms from the remains of the fireball, ash, & dust of the initial explosion kilometers into the air, casting a dark shadow over the city  This draws in fresh air around the ruined city violently, further destroying buildings, & feeding the fires.  12/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: The shockwave weakens as it travels outwards, but some 175 km² get leveled like a house of cards falling.  This traps tens of thousands who managed to avoid the thermal pulse.  The loss of significant infrastructure sparks fires, contributed to by gas stations exploding.  11/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: It razes human infrastructure. Besides steel reinforced concrete, (which can partially survive this), nothing can withstand it.  Most buildings within a kilometer of the fireball are reduced to their constituent molecules.  9/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: The rapid expansion & the heat of the fireball creates a superheated & super-compressed bubble of air around it.  It then proceeds to expand explosively.  It expands faster than the speed of sound, creating winds far stronger than hurricanes can achieve.  8/🧵
name: Riku 💎 【Ø】

tweet: One moment you're walking your dog in the park, the next, you're on the ground, on fire. Thousands of others will be in the same position, having no time to prepare.  That's just the first phase.  6/🧵
